cs.SI, cs.HC, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.SD 

This paper discusses the transformation of the Web to a participatory medium and the role of social media sites in facilitating new ways of interacting with information. The paper specifically focuses on the photo-sharing site Flickr and how social networks formed through contacts lists enable social browsing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Other likely sub-categories include cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as the paper discusses user interactions with social media sites, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as the paper discusses personalized recommendation systems, cs.MM (Multimedia) as the paper focuses on photo-sharing, and cs.SD (Software Development) as the paper discusses the design and functionality of social media sites.
